The paper discusses the use of social trust in recommender systems, which falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also proposes a method to incorporate predicted trust scores into social matrix factorization models, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on real-world datasets, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC).
